<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Glyphs overflow line box</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#propdef-line-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="internal" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify that glyphs bleed out of the box when 'line-height' is less than the content height." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                width: 200px;
                font-size: 2em;
            }
            #d2
            {
                margin-top: 20px;
                line-height: 0;
                background: green;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the "Filler Text" content is completely visible without any clipping.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2">Filler Text</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>